author: Written by: FOX8Live.com Staff
title: LSP: Body of Alabama man pulled from partially-submerged car nea
text:
PONCHATOULA, LA (WVUE) - Louisiana State troopers are investigating an auto accident that claimed the life of a 25-year-old Alabama man. The incident occurred Tuesday, just before 9:30 a.m. on Highway 51, just south of Ponchatoula. The victim has been identified as Ryan Keith Guidroz of Foley, AL.
According to police, calls came in of an SUV, upside-down and partially underwater off of the right side of the highway. Once the vehicle was removed from the water, investigators found Guidroz's body inside.
Police say that Guidroz was not properly restrained at the time of the incident. Blood samples were taken from Guidroz and will be analyzed at the Louisiana State Police Crime Lab.
The investigation into the incident continues.
